__Pausable_init();\n        __AccessControlEnumerable_init();\n        __UUPSUpgradeable_init();\n        __ReentrancyGuard_init();\n\n        _grantRole(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, TIMELOCK_ADDRESS);\n        // do some initialize and will renounce after initialize\n        _grantRole(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, admin);\n        _grantRole(ADMIN_ROLE, admin);\n        _grantRole(PAUSE_ROLE, admin);\n      uint256 deltaT;\n        unchecked {\n            deltaT = (VESTING_PERIOD - timeSinceLastDistribution);\n        }\n        return (deltaT * lastReward) / VESTING_PERIOD;\n    }\n\n    function lastReward = amount;\n        emit RewardDispatched(amount, block.timestamp, VESTING_PERIOD);\n proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.
